abstract: The bill took shape last year as a way to persuade trade skeptics to support a measure enhancing the president’s power to make global trade deals.
snippet: The bill took shape last year as a way to persuade trade skeptics to support a measure enhancing the president’s power to make global trade deals.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate gave overwhelming final approval Thursday to the most comprehensive overhaul of customs law in decades, giving presidents new tools to combat unfair trade, yet falling short of bipartisan demands for penalties against other nations that manipulate their currencies.

abstract: When Arcade Fire won in 2011 — and shocked nearly everyone, including the band — the award went to music that was new and worthy, not hit-driven.
snippet: When Arcade Fire won in 2011 — and shocked nearly everyone, including the band — the award went to music that was new and worthy, not hit-driven.
lead_paragraph: Long-shot wins, unscripted moments and strange celebrity interactions are among the best reasons to watch awards shows like the Grammys, which are on CBS on Monday. The album of the year category is where they turn up surprisingly often.

headline_main: Beyoncé, the Past Is Calling, and It’s Lady Gaga

abstract: The Super Bowl’s halftime show has changed, really changed. A brief history, from Grambling State’s marching band to Beyoncé and Coldplay.
snippet: The Super Bowl’s halftime show has changed, really changed. A brief history, from Grambling State’s marching band to Beyoncé and Coldplay.
lead_paragraph: During the 2015 Super Bowl halftime show, 118.5 million viewers watched Katy Perry ride onto the field on a giant metallic lion, change costumes three times and soar above the crowd as fireworks bombarded the sky. But it wasn’t always this way: Over the past 50 years, the break between halves of the N.F.L.’s championship game has transformed from a showcase for college sousaphonists into a global marketing opportunity for pop superstars. This is how a 12-minute pause on the field evolved into a barometer of American pop culture in a dozen pivotal performances.

abstract: Research generally confirms what many voters perhaps always intuited: that wealth changes political leaders qualitatively.
snippet: Research generally confirms what many voters perhaps always intuited: that wealth changes political leaders qualitatively.
lead_paragraph: The debate over widening inequality, and what to do about it, has gradually moved toward the center of the political agenda and fueled populist movements on the left and the right in many nations.

abstract: A number of players can claim to be the one who created the shot that revolutionized basketball, but many students of the game give the distinction to Sailors.
snippet: A number of players can claim to be the one who created the shot that revolutionized basketball, but many students of the game give the distinction to Sailors.
lead_paragraph: There was just one witness to the moment Kenny Sailors helped revolutionize the game of basketball — his brother, Bud — but by all accounts, no one has ever doubted their story.

abstract: His initial venture into presidential politics both installed Mr. Cruz as a creature of the Republican establishment and helped begin his divorce from it.
snippet: His initial venture into presidential politics both installed Mr. Cruz as a creature of the Republican establishment and helped begin his divorce from it.
lead_paragraph: In late November 2000, with senior aides to George W. Bush holed up in Tallahassee, Fla., navigating the thickets of election law, a 29-year-old domestic policy adviser named Ted Cruz was given a humbling task: Walk a stack of papers to Federal District Court.
